{
    "word": "Guerdon",
    "definitions": [
        "A reward; requital; recompense; -- used in both a good and a bad sense.",
        "To give guerdon to; to reward; to be a recompense for."
    ],
    "examples": [
        "So young as to regard men's frown or smile As loss or guerdon of a glorious lot.",
        "He shall, by thy revenging hand, at once receive the just guerdon of all his former villainies.",
        "Him we gave a costly bribe To guerdon silence."
    ],
    "etymology": "[OF. guerdon, guerredon, LL. widerdonum (influenced by L. donum gift, cf. Donation ), fr. OHG. widarl; widar again, against (G. wider wieder) + l reward, G. lohn, akin to AS. le Goth. laun. See Withers.]"
}